7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Copy.ai and Grammarly share a solid foundation of core features including Short Form, Tone Control, Api Access, Team Collaboration. Where Copy.ai pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Long Form and Templates and Multilingual, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Grammarly uniquely offers Plagiarism Check and Browser Extension, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Copy.ai holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Grammarly scores 8/10 overall and 10/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Copy.ai and Grammarly offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Copy.ai's free tier and Grammarly's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
