b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Copy.ai is best suited for sales copy, social media posts, email sequences, workflow automation, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Grammarly, meanwhile, shines for grammar checking, professional emails, academic writing, tone detection, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, Copy.ai describes itself as \"AI-powered copywriting and workflow automation platform.\" Grammarly, established in 2009, positions itself as \"The world's most popular AI writing and grammar checker.\" With 11 years between them, Grammarly brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Copy.ai offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Grammarly** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Copy.ai is a poor choice — far from it. Copy.ai excels in its own right, particularly for sales copy and social media posts.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value industry-leading grammar and style checking, go with Grammarly. If generous free plan with 2000 words/month matters more to you, Copy.ai is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
